          </h3>
          <ul
            style="color: #e0e0e0; line-height: 1.8; list-style: none; padding: 0;"
          >
            <li>‚Ä¢ Tendency toward dogmatism</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Impatience with slower learners</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Restlessness and wanderlust</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Overconfidence in beliefs</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Difficulty with routine tasks</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Can be preachy or judgmental</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="color: #ffa500; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-size: 1.2rem;">
            Spiritual Significance
          </h3>
          <ul
            style="color: #e0e0e0; line-height: 1.8; list-style: none; padding: 0;"
          >
            <li>‚Ä¢ Represents the seeker of truth</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Connection to higher realms</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Guardian of sacred knowledge</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Bridge between human and divine</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Symbol of spiritual evolution</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Protector of dharmic principles</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        style="margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem; background: rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.03); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.1);"
      >
        <h3
          style="color: #ffa500; margin-bottom: 1rem; text-align: center; font-size: 1.4rem;"
        >
          Mantra & Sacred Connection
        </h3>
        <p
          style="text-align: center; font-size: 1.1rem; color: #e0e0e0; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-style: italic;"
        >
          "‡•ê ‡§ó‡•Å‡§∞‡§µ‡•á ‡§®‡§Æ‡§É" (Om Gurave Namah)
        </p>
        <p style="text-align: center; color: #999999; line-height: 1.7;">
          This mantra honors Jupiter (Guru), the ruling planet of Sagittarius,
          invoking wisdom, guidance, and spiritual enlightenment. Chanting this
          mantra while observing Sagittarius is believed to enhance one's
          connection to higher knowledge and dharmic path.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</ConstellationLayout>

<script>
  import ConstellationFramework from "@layouts/Constellation/js/ConstellationFramework";

  try {
    // Initialize Sagittarius constellation with enhanced configuration
    const sagittariusConfig = ConstellationFramework.createConstellationConfig(
      "Sagittarius",
      {
        ra: "RA: 19h 00m",
        dec: "Dec: -25¬∞",
        raDescription:
          "Right Ascension coordinates for Sagittarius constellation center",
        decDescription:
          "Declination coordinates for Sagittarius constellation center",
        starData: {
          "Kaus Australis":
            "The brightest star in Sagittarius, a blue giant star 145 light-years away.",
          "Kaus Media":
            'An orange giant star, part of the "bow" of the archer.',
          "Kaus Borealis": "An orange supergiant, completing the archer's bow.",
          Nunki:
            "The second brightest star, a hot blue star 228 light-years away.",
          Ascella: "A close binary star system in the archer's arm.",
          Shaula:
            "A blue supergiant, one of the hottest stars visible to the naked eye.",
          Nash: "A red giant star in the archer's body.",
          Albaldah: "An orange giant star marking the archer's knee.",
        },
        enableTypingEffect: true,
        enableMouseTrail: true,
        enableParallax: true,
      },
    );

    new ConstellationFramework(sagittariusConfig);

    ConstellationFramework.addNebulaTooltips(
      "A nebula is a giant cloud of dust and gas in space where stars are born, live, and die. Sagittarius contains some of the most spectacular nebulae visible from Earth.",
    );
  } catch (err) {
    console.error("Error initializing Sagittarius constellation:", err);
  }
</script>
